
Glulxe 0.5.0 for the Amiga
--------------------------

This is Andrew Plotkin's interpreter for Glulx format text adventure games,
Glulxe, ported to the Amiga by David Kinder. Glulx is one of the formats
produced by the Inform text adventure creation system.

Glulx games can be found on the Internet: see

  http://www.ifarchive.org/indexes/if-archiveXgamesXglulx.html
  http://ifdb.tads.org/search?searchfor=system%3Ainform

For more information on what Glulx is, see Andrew's page

  http://eblong.com/zarf/glulx/index.html

Kickstart 2.04 or higher is required.

This program includes software (specifically, parts of the BigNum library
from OpenSSL) written by Eric Young (eay@cryptsoft.com).
